# DCA OS Lite - Cline Rules

These are the operating rules for AI-assisted work in this repository.

## Project context

- Project: DCA OS Lite
- Frontend: React + Vite + TypeScript
- Backend: Node.js + Express
- Database: Prisma + PostgreSQL
- Runtime/development topology: Docker Compose + Caddy reverse proxy
- Local platform: Windows
- Shell policy: PowerShell only
- Local repo path: C:\dcaosv1
- Local API port: 4000
- Local web port: 5173

## Hard rules

- Do not touch production deployment files unless explicitly requested.
- Do not modify package manifests, Prisma schema, source code, or tests unless explicitly requested.
- Do not modify Docker/Caddy config unless explicitly requested.
- Do not read, edit, print, or expose `.env` secrets.
- Do not run `npm audit fix --force`.
- Do not run destructive git commands unless explicitly requested.
- Do not run production deploy commands.
- Before editing auth, API, or Prisma startup code, verify `.env` is loaded before importing app, auth, or Prisma modules.
- Never change login or auth behavior until local env boot order is confirmed.
- Always use Windows PowerShell commands.
- Always keep changes small and scoped.
- Always show `git diff --stat` before recommending a commit.
- Always include repeatable PowerShell smoke and validation scripts as part of workflow deliverables when adding stability, validation, smoke tests, or module workflow.
- Treat scripts as part of the deliverable, not optional documentation.
- Stop after 2 failed attempts on the same runtime error.
- Stop if a migration would drop columns or tables.
- Stop if files outside allowed scope are modified.
- No broad module builds. Use small sealed work blocks.

## Validation commands

Use these commands when validating work:

```powershell
npm run validate
npm run smoke:local
npm run smoke:browser
npx prisma validate
npx prisma migrate status
```

## Browser smoke rule

- Playwright smoke must be used to detect browser/runtime failures.
- Browser smoke must pass before feature work is considered complete.

## Production rule

- Never recommend production deployment until local validation and browser smoke pass.
